Security
Scam e-mails and fake websites
You may receive e-mails that look like they've come from Man Numeric (“Numeric”) or a Man Group entity which direct you to a fake website asking to disclose all of your security information.
Do not respond to the e-mail or visit any website linked from such e-mails. Be warned, these can appear to be genuine.
Neither Numeric nor any Man Group entity will ever ask you to disclose all your personal or security details by e-mail.
 
